cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to remove the effect of haze from images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a multi-scale Convolutional Neural Network for learning the mapping between hazy images and their corresponding transmittance maps and environmental illumination, which suggests the possibility of it being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the estimation of environmental illumination, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Overall, the paper's focus on image dehazing and the use of deep learning techniques makes cs.CV the most likely category, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.GR, and cs.MM.
